org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a

Class InconsistentAmazonS3Client

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amazonaws.AmazonWebServiceClient
      • com.amazonaws.services.s3.AmazonS3Client
        • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.InconsistentAmazonS3Client
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.amazonaws.services.s3.AmazonS3, com.amazonaws.services.s3.internal.S3DirectSpi

    @InterfaceAudience.Private
 @InterfaceStability.Unstable
public class InconsistentAmazonS3Client
extends com.amazonaws.services.s3.AmazonS3Client
    A wrapper around AmazonS3 that injects inconsistency and/or errors. Used for testing S3Guard. Currently only delays listing visibility, not affecting GET.

      • clearInconsistency

        public void clearInconsistency()
        Clear all oustanding inconsistent keys. After calling this function, listings should behave normally (no failure injection), until additional keys are matched for delay, e.g. via putObject(), deleteObject().
